         Mine would have to be hill giants. Specifically, the hill giants in the rathe mountains. Their low magic resistance and barely average hp combined with their large amounts of platinum makes them absoutely DEADLY. Usually I have to bring a group containing the holy trinity to take them down: A druid, a ranger, and a mage.</P><P>Man, if they make another mob like hill giants, I'll hang up my scythe and make a shaman, because another hill giantesque mob would certainly be a harbinger of the end of soloing.<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
