         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>And where are the spiders in Nurga?  Greatest Necro solo spot, highly discussed on this board, and completely nerfed in the last patch.</P><P>Don't fool yourself for a moment that Big Brother is not watching.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Correct me if I'm wrong, but...<BR><ul><li>The spiders in Nurga have been there forever.  They've been being discussed for at least a year, since I started reading the forums here.  This being the case, this wasn't a quick, '<font color=red>look the Necromancers have found somewhere to hunt, nerf it right now</font id=red>,' situation, was it?</li><BR><li>Haven't Verant been talking about upgrading Droga and Nurga since way back when they did Chardok?  I've never seen any official Verant remark, true, but I recall it being discussed here a long time ago.</li><BR><li>There's a post in the Hunting Guide forum that states the goblins that have replaced the spiders are the same level range as the spiders they replaced.  And, that you can hunt them in exactly the same way you would've hunted the spiders.  Is this not the case?</li></ul></P><P>I don't doubt that people from Verant visit these boards.  They post here, on rare occaisions, so they're not exactly hiding!</P><P>And equally, I don't doubt that if they see something that is horribly wrong, they'll probably fix it.  <i>(Instantly refreshing your spell gems, by clicking JBoots, for example.)</i>  But unless something is being exploited, or is waaaay outta line, I really doubt they particularly care.  </P><P>Regardless of what you think, Verant don't pay a 'Necromancer nerfer'.  Necromancer issues don't get fixed, not because they hate us, but because they couldn't give a crap.  But, suprising as you might find it, that's how businesses work.  They don't give a crap about any of the other classes either!  The only difference, is that a class with more active players can generate more noise.</P><P>Aside from which, regardless of whether you, or I am right in this, my original point remains valid.  If you take the attitude that nothing should be discussed, because it might be nerfed, then The Vision might as well remove the boards and be done with it.</P><P>AlAaraaf.</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
